               <msContents class="lemmatic">
                  <summary>This manuscript contains commentary on the book of Aphorisms attributed to <persName type="standard" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/287984736" key="person_287984736">Hippocrates</persName>.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_4791-item1">
                     <author key="person_4405945">
                        <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/4405945" type="aut">Ibn Abī Ṣādiq‏ابن أبي صادق</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_7754">Commentary on Hippocratic Aphorisms</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_7754">شرح فصول أبقراط</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="alt" key="work_7754">Sharḥ Fuṣūl Abuqrāṭ</title>
                     <note>Original manuscript in Majlis-i Shurá-yi Islāmī Library.</note>
                     <note>This is a Persian version of Ibn Abī Ṣādiq's commentary (i.e., Arabic lemmata, and Persion translation of the lemmata and Ibn Abī Ṣādiq's commentary). The first few folios are missing; MS starts in the middle of i. 1; the beginning of each Book is as follows: Bk2: 25a; Bk3: 48b; Bk4: 68b; Bk5: 104a; Bk6: 139a; Bk7: 172b; Then it ends at a middle of comm. on vii. 56; last few folios are missing.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
